The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The problems studied in the paper involve covering objects, which suggests that it may belong to the subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and optimization problems, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses decomposition methods and threshold mechanisms, which are techniques commonly used in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
